## Labels & Selectors

### Label Operations
```bash
kubectl label pod <pod-name> app=myapp      # Add label to pod
kubectl label pod <pod-name> app=myapp --overwrite  # Update label
kubectl label pod <pod-name> app-            # Remove label
kubectl label pods -l app=oldlabel app=newlabel  # Label multiple pods
kubectl get pods --show-labels               # Show all labels
kubectl get pods -L app,version              # Show specific labels as columns
```

### Selector Queries
```bash
kubectl get pods -l app=myapp                # Select by label
kubectl get pods -l 'app in (app1, app2)'    # Select with IN operator
kubectl get pods -l 'app,version!=1.0'       # Multiple selectors
kubectl get pods -l '!app'                   # Select without label
```

## Resource Quotas & Limits

### Resource Management
```bash
kubectl get resourcequota                    # List ResourceQuotas
kubectl describe resourcequota <name>        # Get details
kubectl create resourcequota <name> --hard=pods=10,cpu=20,memory=40Gi
