## Apply & Diff

### Apply Operations
```bash
kubectl apply -f <file.yaml>                 # Apply YAML
kubectl apply -f <directory>                 # Apply all files in directory
kubectl apply -f <url>                       # Apply from URL
kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f <file.yaml>  # Dry run
kubectl diff -f <file.yaml>                  # Show differences
kubectl replace -f <file.yaml>               # Replace resource
kubectl delete -f <file.yaml>                # Delete from file
```

## Patch & Edit

### Patch Operations
```bash
kubectl patch pod <pod-name> -p '{"spec":{"activeDeadlineSeconds":300}}'
kubectl patch pod <pod-name> --type merge -p '{"spec":{"activeDeadlineSeconds":300}}'
kubectl patch pod <pod-name> --type strategic -p '{"spec":{"activeDeadlineSeconds":300}}'
kubectl patch serviceaccount <sa> -p '{"imagePullSecrets": [{"name": "myregistry"}]}'
```

### Edit Commands
```bash
kubectl edit pod <pod-name>                  # Edit pod in default editor
kubectl edit deployment <deployment>         # Edit deployment
kubectl edit service <service>               # Edit service
kubectl set env deployment/<dep> VAR=value   # Set environment variables
kubectl set resources deployment/<dep> --limits=cpu=500m --requests=cpu=250m
```

## Kustomize Commands

### Kustomize Operations
```bash
kubectl apply -k <directory>                 # Apply Kustomization
